Rarely does the world of dance music produce a band that can equally perform as powerful a live show as create a classic club track.Faithless are one of those few who not only do both, 
but have the catalogue of hits to produce an awesome Greatest Hits Tour.

Formed in 1995 from core members Rollo and DJ Sister Bliss, Faithless were joined by rapper Maxi Jazz and guitarist Dave Randall in the original line up. With occasional input from 
Rollo's sister Dido, who would go on to become a multi million selling artist in her own right, Faithless soon hit the charts all over the world with tracks such as "Salva Mea", Insomnia",
and "Don't Leave" which culminated in their hit debut album "Reverence." In 1998 faithless scored a further UK top ten single with "God Is A DJ" and subsequent hits "Take The Long Way Home,"
and "Bring My Family Back" from the hit album "Sunday 8pm". They enjoyed even further success in 2001 with hit singles "We Come 1", and "Muhammad Ali", and "One Step Too Far" (featuring Dido) 
from the hit album "Outrospective" which reached number four in the UK album charts.

In 2004 Faithless secured their place in dance music greatness with a number one album in "No Roots." Further hit singles "Mass Destruction", "I Want More" were followed in 2005 with "Forever Faithless
- The Greatest Hits" and the 2006 album "To All New Arrivals" Successive world tours have enshrined their popularity all over the globe andthis is clearly evident as they delight their Moscow fans as 
part of this Greatest Hits Tour.
